<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Java Mastery with Gemini</title>
    <style>
        :root {
            --java-orange: #f89820;
            --java-blue: #5382a1;
            --dark-bg: #23272e;
        }
        body {
            font-family: 'Segoe UI', sans-serif;
            background-color: #f4f7f6;
            color: #333;
            margin: 0;
            display: flex;
        }
        nav {
            width: 250px;
            background: var(--dark-bg);
            color: white;
            height: 100vh;
            padding: 20px;
            position: fixed;
        }
        main {
            margin-left: 290px;
            padding: 40px;
            max-width: 800px;
        }
        .code-block {
            background: #282c34;
            color: #abb2bf;
            padding: 15px;
            border-radius: 5px;
            font-family: 'Consolas', monospace;
            overflow-x: auto;
            border-left: 5px solid var(--java-orange);
        }
        .keyword { color: #c678dd; }
        .class-name { color: #e5c07b; }
        .string { color: #98c379; }
        .badge {
            background: var(--java-blue);
            color: white;
            padding: 5px 12px;
            border-radius: 20px;
            font-size: 0.8rem;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

    <nav>
        <h2>☕ Java Docs</h2>
        <ul style="list-style: none; padding: 0;">
            <li><a href="#" style="color: var(--java-orange); text-decoration: none;">1. Introduction</a></li>
            <li><a href="#" style="color: white; text-decoration: none;">2. Variables</a></li>
            <li><a href="#" style="color: white; text-decoration: none;">3. OOP Principles</a></li>
        </ul>
    </nav>

    <main>
        <header>
            <span class="badge">Version: JDK 21</span>
            <h1>Getting Started with Java</h1>
            <p>Welcome to the tutorial! Today is <%= new Date().toLocaleDateString() %> — a perfect day to code.</p>
        </header>

        <section>
            <h3>The Classic "Hello World"</h3>
            <p>In Java, every line of code that can be executed must be inside a <strong>class</strong>.</p>
            
            <div class="code-block">
                <pre>
<span class="keyword">public class</span> <span class="class-name">Main</span> {
    <span class="keyword">public static void</span> main(String[] args) {
        System.out.println(<span class="string">"Hello, Gemini!"</span>);
    }
}</pre>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section style="margin-top: 40px;">
            <h3>Quick Tip</h3>
            <blockquote>
                Java is <strong>statically typed</strong>, meaning you must declare the type of a variable when you create it.
            </blockquote>
        </section>
    </main>

</body>
</html>